cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with multi-task learning in natural language understanding (NLU) tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also proposes neural network architectures for this purpose, which indicates that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves encoding different feature spaces at different levels, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category, as multi-task learning is a common technique in computer vision.
